fix: prevent CWD file creation in production mode

- main(): only use CWD as data dir when config_path is absolute.
  Otherwise resolve to ~/.slife/ (production) or CWD (dev via get_data_dir).
  Config path also resolved to the correct location, preventing accidental
  slife.json5 creation in CWD.
- system_health.py: use get_data_dir() instead of hardcoded Path("slife.json5")
- skill.py: delegate _resolve_skills_dir to paths.get_skills_dir()
- subagent/process.py: use get_config_path() fallback

Co-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
